{{Infobox person | name = Françoise Balibar | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Françoise Dumesnil | birth_date = {{Birth year and age|1941}} | birth_place = [[France]] | death_date = | death_place = | residence = | nationality = | education = | alma_mater = [[École Normale Supérieure]] | occupation = [[Physicist]], [[epistemologist]] | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | television = | religion = <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | spouse = [[Étienne Balibar]] | children = [[Jeanne Balibar]] | awards = | signature = | website = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} --> | footnotes = }}
'''Françoise Balibar''' (born '''Françoise Dumesnil''' in 1941) is a French [[physicist]] and [[science historian]], a [[professor emeritus]] at [[Paris Diderot University]].<ref name=culture>{{cite web |url=https://www.franceculture.fr/personne/francoise-balibar |title=Françoise Balibar |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=[[France Culture]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-02-08 |language=fr}}</ref> She has extensively published works on [[Albert Einstein]], the [[theory of relativity]], the [[History of physics|history]] and [[epistemology]] of [[physics]].
== Biography == Françoise Balibar studied at [[École Normale Supérieure]] from 1960 to 1964.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.babelio.com/auteur/Francoise-Balibar/5309 |title=Françoise Balibar (Babelio) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=babelio.com |publisher= |accessdate=2018-02-08 |language=fr}}</ref> She has written numerous articles in national and international journals and led the [[CNRS]] team in charge of six volumes of the French edition of Einstein’s selected works.<ref name=culture /> She is also the author of several books, including ''The Science of Crystals'' and ''Einstein: Decoding the Universe''.
She is the wife of the philosopher [[Étienne Balibar]] and the mother of the actress [[Jeanne Balibar]]. She has appeared in two films: ''{{ill|Mange ta soupe|fr}}'' in 1997 and ''[[Modern Life (film)|Modern Life]]'' in 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0050209/ |title=Françoise Balibar, Actress |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=[[imdb.com]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-02-08}}</ref>
